# orbit is a PUBLIC repo. The STRUCTURE (docs, skills, contract, fixtures) is
# versioned; real work CONTENT is NEVER committed. Two walls enforce that.
# (CLAUDE.md non-goal: "No corporate data in this repo.")

# ── Wall 1: deny-by-default inside every numbered area. ─────────────────────
# Nothing under an area folder is ever tracked except its .gitkeep keepalive,
# so a work file dropped in ANY format (not just known binaries) cannot leak.
# When you add a new area, add its two lines here (part of the SPEC change order).
00-inbox/**
10-daily/**
20-design/**
30-operations/**
40-projects/**
50-policy/**
!00-inbox/.gitkeep
!10-daily/.gitkeep
!20-design/.gitkeep
!30-operations/.gitkeep
!40-projects/.gitkeep
!50-policy/.gitkeep

# ── Wall 2: block payload binary extensions ANYWHERE (belt & suspenders). ───
# Catches binaries dropped outside a numbered area too (e.g. a stray root file).
*.pptx
*.ppt
*.xlsx
*.xls
*.docx
*.doc
*.pdf
*.zip
*.7z
*.msg
*.eml
*.png
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.gif
*.vsdx

# fixtures and skills are skeleton — always tracked (re-includes past Wall 2)
!tests/**
!skills/**

# generated output — regenerate via skills/orbit-dashboard/generate.py
dashboard.html
# per-area browsing cards (NN-*/README.md) are also generated — regenerate via
# skills/area-architect/generate_cards.py. Already denied by Wall 1 above (area
# folders track only .gitkeep), listed here only so their absence from git is expected.

# machine-local skill wiring: junctions into Claude Code's discovery root.
# skills/ stays canonical; recreate the links with `python .claude/setup-skills.py`.
.claude/skills/

# OS noise
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
__pycache__/
